Do you not have &#39;Hashmap&#39; or even &#39;Vector&#39; ?

Seems to me you&#39;re doing a sequential search of an array, which is O(n), not so good. 

Instead, you could have an an array of arraylists, and make use of the hashcode. Something like:

    List&lt;String&gt;[] arrayLists = new List[100];
    {
        for (int i=0; i&lt;100; i++) arrayLists[i] = new ArrayList();
    }

     public void store(String URL){
        arrayLists[URL.hashCode()%arrayLists.length].add(URL);
     }
    
     public boolean find (String URL) {
            List&lt;String&gt; myArrayList = arrayLists[URL.toLowerCase().hashCode()%arrayLists.length];
    
            for (int i = 0; i &lt; myArrayList.size(); i++) {
                if (URL.equalsIgnoreCase(myArrayList.get(i))) {
                    return true;
                }
            }
            
            return false;
     }

This should give you a complexity of O(N/arrayLists.length) - As the length of arrayLists approach the length of your number of URL&#39;s, complexity would fall to O(1) worse case.

