Since you know the direction in which the missiles should fly (the red line), the distance from the center position (e.g. 10) and you know that there is a 90&#176; angle between the movement vector of the missile (red line) and the connection line between the two starting positions of the missiles (marked as black line in the image) you can calculate the resulting positions like this:

